name: A Dance of Fire and Ice

editorialNotes.standard: Bursting with catchy tunes and googly-eyed foodstuffs, this embellished account of the PB&J sandwich’s creation is weird in all the right ways.

Thumper: Pocket Edition is utterly mesmerizing. It's a brutal test of reaction time and an awe-inspiring dive into kaleidoscopic dreamscapes. Or, perhaps more accurately, into nightmares. The music and sound effects swell and pound with ominous tension, making this blistering sprint through light and writhing shapes feel like a vital struggle for survival. Music games rarely squeeze your emotions in such a menacing grip.
editorialNotes.short: An intense, surprisingly frightening mix of action and music.

ios.subtitle: Let the rhythm fill your soul

editorialNotes.standard: This chilled-out title has a rhythm all of its own. By dropping tiny spirits into place, you’re not just solving the puzzle – you’re adding beats to the jam. Sit back, pop on your headphones and enjoy the relaxed grooves as you work your way through some delightfully animated levels.

ios.subtitle: Run, jump and roll to the beat

editorialNotes.short: Try your luck getting past each challenging level for free this month.
editorialNotes.tagline: Tap, tap, tap to the beat

editorialNotes.standard: Absolutely exploding with style and energy, this infinite jumper challenges you to guide little leaping block people up, up and away into musical heaven. Using taps to hurl your angular avatars from one shifting platform to the next, you’ll aim for boosts that’ll rocket them even higher—or at least keep them from plunging to their game-ending doom. With pulsing electronic music and eyeball-caressing neon visuals, it’s like a dance party for your brain. Joyously simple and simply joyous.

name: Piano Notes!  -  Learn To Read Music
Give It Up! - Jump to the Beat

editorialNotes.standard: Harmony 3’s clean, colorful puzzles are like soothing meditations. The gameplay is simple: move tiles a specified number of times, making sure each one ends in the correct spot. Because you can reset only a single move, the game rewards foresight and planning. While the levels get difficult in a hurry, the tranquil music and relaxing visuals guarantee you’ll take your time on every stage.

editorialNotes.short: Fly through tranquil space and coast on mellow moods.
